DESCRIPTION:The Program in Latino/a Studies in the Global South is excited
  to invite you to a Listening Lunch concert on the Biddle Music Building 
 back patio at 12:30pm on Wednesday\, April 8th!\n\nWith food from Durham'
 s famous Taqueria La Vaquita\, the lunch will feature music from visiting
  musicians Cesar Castro and Chùy Sandoval\, who are steeped in the son ja
 rocho tradition of Veracruz\, Mexico. The maestros are visiting Durham fo
 r the annual  Fandango de Durham on April 11th\, a free community festiva
 l that celebrates son jarocho. We are excited to have them on campus. In 
 anticipation of the Fandango de Durham\, please join us for lunch\, music
 \, and convivencia with students and colleagues!
DURATION:PT1H
