CREATED:20260113T162349Z
DESCRIPTION:Religious faith shapes the lives of billions of people and wor
 ld events\, and all of those major religions are represented at Duke. The
  Interfaith Campus Pilgrimages program invites graduate students to deepe
 n their understanding of these faiths through monthly visits to sacred sp
 aces at Duke and discussions with Religious Life leaders. Students who wi
 sh to can also participate in the rituals\, services\, and practices of t
 hese faith groups. \n\nThis pilgrimage is to Duke Gardens\, a 55-acre bot
 anic garden in the heart of Duke University that inspires transformative 
 learning\, promotes wellness and builds community.\n\nSign up at https://
 duke.is/p/4ag7 .\n\nLearn more at: https://chapel.duke.edu/student-engage
 ment/religious-life-duke/interfaith-engagement/duke-interfaith-campus-pil
 grimages/ .\n\n\nThe pilgrimages are presented by Duke Chapel and Religio
 us Life at Duke in conjunction with the QuadEx Chaplains program.
DURATION:PT1H
DTSTAMP:20260113T162349Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260408T163000
LAST-MODIFIED:20260113T162349Z
